GLENROSA travelled near the rear two wide down the backstretch, saved ground through the turn, burst between foes in the four path in mid stretch and determinedly won the fight for third money at the wire. DANISH SKY settled in midpack outside three deep down the backside, could not quicken with others three wide on the turn, shifted out to be in the five path turning for home and dueled to the wire for the show award just missing in a photo. UNDER BUDGET could see the field with four furlongs to run, could not make any headway to rivals throughout the turn, shifted out six wide in upper stretch and passed tired runners down the lane. PRINCESS O DENMARK was hustled early to press for the lead inside with a half mile remaining, could not find more giving way up front midpoint on the turn, and retreated inside in mid stretch. BOSTON MABEL was reined back to watch the top pair engage at the half, was roused three wide outside runners at the quarter pole to be in range in the four path at the top of the lane and stopped with horses on either side in the final furlong.

RACE.FOOTNOTES: DIOSA CATRINA settled toward the back switching off the rail, advanced outside foes four to five wide turning into upper stretch, rallied outside and edged past late under steady handling. WELL ACTUALLY stalked two to three wide, drew even prompting the pace about the seven-sixteenths, took charge at the five-sixteenths, drifted out a bit turning into upper stretch, was outkicked but kept on well enough to maintain the place. LA PRINCESSA POLLY shifted in tracking in behind the leaders just off the fence, came out three wide turning for home, bid between runners, kept on late inside but needed more. VIVID VIXEN settled off the pace and outside two to three deep, gradually advanced on the far turn, shifted to the rail near the furlong grounds, altered out late as room on the rail became tight, ran on evenly. P. S. RISING STAR raced off the pace in the two to three path, went evenly and made no bid. NO MORE DIAMONDS was a bit rank and pulling keenly early setting the pace, was pressured by an outside rival into the far turn, faded in the stretch. HELLUVA HOLIDAY lacked early speed, dropped well back heading up the backstretch, swung six wide, passed tired foes. TARA LUNA raced in the back of the field mostly three to four wide, failed to menace. THATSITTHATSALL was outside foes mid-pack three to four wide early, tired.
